article.headline: Alcorn St. 59, Alabama A&M 58
article.story: NORMAL, Ala. (AP) -- Cornell Landry scored 14 points to help Alcorn State beat Alabama A&M 59-58 on Saturday night. LaNorris Smith led Alabama A&M (6-11) with 16 points, including hitting four of seven 3-pointers. Alcorn State (5-13) committed 26 turnovers, but outrebounded Alabama A&M 51-33. Alabama A&M had a chance to win the game, but Trant Simpson missed a 3-pointer with 10 seconds left.
